            This is a webspace of USC students, postdocs, staff, and faculty doing research in astrophysics and cosmology. 
            We come together in a variety of weekly meetings: 
            In CosmoLab (Thursdays), we review new papers and discuss progress and current issues related to research and academia, with occasional zoom talks by researchers from other institutions.  
            In CosmoLab <a href="https://github.com/usc-cosmolab/hackspace">Hacks</a> and we hack together on Discord platform. 
            In <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Talks">USC Cosmology Seminar</a> (on Fridays), we host formal 1-hour talks by internal and external researchers. 
            You can contact gluscevi[at]usc.edu if you'd like to join any of our meetings.
            </p>
        
